<ns6320:section xmlns:ns6320="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.exceptionHandling.chaining.implementChaining.implementChaining">  
  <ns6321:title xmlns:ns6321="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Implementing exception chaining</ns6321:title>
    <ns6322:para xmlns:ns6322="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Implement exception chaining by following these guidelines:
        <ns6323:itemizedlist xmlns:ns6323="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">           
            <ns6324:listitem xmlns:ns6324="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns6325:para xmlns:ns6325="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Define your own exception class. Create a custom exception class as a child class of 
                    java.lang.Exception or any other Exception subclass. 
                </ns6325:para>
            </ns6324:listitem>
            <ns6326:listitem xmlns:ns6326="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns6327:para xmlns:ns6327="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    No other custom code is required because java chains one cause to another automatically 
                    by means of the constructor. Define a constructor that takes a Throwable as an argument.
                </ns6327:para>
            </ns6326:listitem>
        </ns6323:itemizedlist>   
    </ns6322:para>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" href="examples/examples.docbook"/>
    </ns6320:section>